<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-07-16T11:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-07-16T11:40:00-05:00" n="606" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/2438:Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-07-16T12:00:00-04:40"><hi rend="italic">July 16,
                                        1924—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 11:05
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>41. Your 28, July 11, 3 p.m. Nominations of Ariza and Alvarez<note n="21" xml:id="d606fn21">Frederico G. Alvarez, Secretary of the Dominican
                                Legation.</note> confirmed by the Senate yesterday and Dominican
                            Government complying with the formalities of the occasion desire to know
                            whether Ariza is <hi rend="italic">persona grata</hi>. Matter of
                            short-time loan of two and one half millions<note n="22" xml:id="d606fn22">The same loan that had previously been proposed
                                for $2,000,000.</note> was presented to Congress and referred to
                            Finance Committee of the Senate.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>